Topic: Topics are the fundamental organizing units of information in a Canopy project. Topics are for modeling ideas or entities that can be explained alone without prior context, as opposed to [[subtopic|subtopics]]. A topic in Canopy is composed of a [[topic name]], and a [[topic paragraph]], like this one. In the Canopy interface, a topic corresponds to a paragraph that either appears first on the page, or after a dividing line. The  The data of a topic is stored in a [[topic file]]. Every project must have a [[default topic]]. It is a best practice to know [[when to use topics versus subtopics]].
